snippet.textDisplay: Not-so-fun fact: anxious dogs often don't want to lie down because that puts them in a vulnerable position which is scary for them. Making them do it is a great way to make your dog hate "down"... and training in general. Pushing a dog  onto their side is not "teaching" them, and anyone with basic knowledge of dog body language can see that both dogs are confused and stressed throughout the video. But I suppose that doesn't matter to the people who make these kinds of videos as much as how many likes the video will get.
